oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Tennessee Highway Department employees mulch a road bank with straw to hold and protect the new seeding of fescue and clover. This mulch was supplied by the Knox County Council of Garden Clubs through the Knox County Soil Conservation District.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Caption: "Not a cannon or a secret weapon, but a mechanical mulcher spreading straw was paid for by the Knox County Garden Clubs. This machine accomplishes in minutes work that would take hours by hand labor."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Glen W. Harrison, SCS
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Government employees; Roads; Soil conservation; Agricultural machinery & implements; Organizations
